ritics.com/dfw-film-critics-pick-1917-as-best-film-of-2019/| title=DFW Film Critics Pick \"1917\" as Best Film of 2019| publisher=[[Dallas\u2013Fort Worth Film Critics Association]] | date= December 16, 2019| accessdate=December 16, 2019 | author= Jorgenson, Todd}}</ref> \n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| December 16, 2019\n| [[Dallas\u2013Fort Worth Film Critics Association Award for Best Actress#2010s|Best Actress]]\n| [[Lupita Nyong'o]]\n| {{no|5th Place}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Detroit Film Critics Society]]<ref name=\"dfcs19\">{{cite web | url=https://detroitfilmcritics.com/the-2019-detroit-film-critics-society-awards-nominations/| title=The 2019 Detroit Film Critics Society Awards Nominations| publisher=[[Detroit Film Critics Society Awards]]| accessdate=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Detroit Film Critics Society#2019|December 9, 2019]]\n| Best Actress\n| [[Lupita Nyong'o]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Dorian Awards]]<ref name=\"DA20\">{{cite web | url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-gay-lesbian-entertainment-critics-dorian-awards-noms-full-list-1265575 | title='Parasite,' 'Portrait of a Lady on Fire,' 'Pain and Glory' Lead Dorian Award Nominations| publisher=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date=January 3, 2020 | accessdate=January 3, 2020 | author= Beresford,Trilby}}</ref>\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|January 8, 2020\n| Film Performance of the Year - Actress\n| [[Lupita Nyong'o]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Dublin Film Critics' Circle]]<ref name=\"dfcc19\">{{cite web | url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/film/the-best-movie-of-2019-according-to-irish-film-critics-1.4118496| title=The best movie of 2019, according to Irish film critics | publisher=[[The Irish Times]]| accessdate=December 17, 2019|author= Clarke, Donald}}</ref> \n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" style=\